00:22:39,061 --> 00:22:43,920
在这里，德国空军的精英第一次看到了Me-262
It was here that the cream of the German Luftwaffe and saw the Me-262 for the first time.

276
00:22:47,671 --> 00:22:50,010
我们第一次看到飞机的时候都震惊了
We were surprised when we first saw it standing there.

277
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:55,080
机炮简直不可思议
The guns were incredible,

278
00:22:55,081 --> 00:22:58,470
训练这些飞行员成了最优先事项
the training of these pilots was given top priority,

279
00:22:58,471 --> 00:23:00,360
但随着战争潮水涌来
But with the tide of war running against them,

280
00:23:00,361 --> 00:23:02,640
已经没有时间进行战术教学了
there was little time for classroom tactics.

281
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,660
训练非常短暂，仅有四个半日的课程
The training was a very simple,four half days of lessons.

282
00:23:10,650 --> 00:23:15,570
然后你就得独自飞行。因为飞机是单座的
Then you had to do your first flight on your own because the machines were single-seaters.

283
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:23,190
我们必须保证不会弄坏飞机
We had to give our word that we would not damage the machines.

284
00:23:23,191 --> 00:23:28,770
否则我们就会受到惩罚或者立即遣送回原岗位
otherwise we would be punished or immediately sent back to the units we came from.

285
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:32,140
这样的警告牢记在心中，
With that warning uppermost in their minds,

286
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:35,970
即便是有经验的飞行员，后续训练也被看做是首飞*
even for these experienced pilots, the first flights were always *never again.

287
00:23:39,481 --> 00:23:45,180
坐在机翼上的士官向我讲解飞机内部，特别是那些要密切注意的地方
The sergeant who was on the wing explained to me the interior of the plane, especially what to look out for.

288
00:23:46,740 --> 00:23:51,960
例如引擎用的汽油必须缓慢加装
For example, the gas for the engine was only *stepped up very slowly,

289
00:23:51,961 --> 00:23:53,400
否则引擎就会熄火
otherwise the engine would stall.

290
00:23:55,230 --> 00:23:59,460
涡轮引擎必须缓慢变速
The turbine engine had to get used to the speed very slowly,

291
00:23:59,461 --> 00:24:00,780
所以必须非常小心
So one had to be very careful.

292
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:13,350
一旦起飞，Me-262将会超越飞行员的期望
Once in the air the experience of flying Me-262 surpassed all their expectations.

293
00:24:13,351 --> 00:24:18,090
对任何狂热的飞行员来说，驾驶这架飞机都是最为非凡的体验
For any pilot passionate about flying. It was a most extraordinary experience,

294
00:24:18,091 --> 00:24:22,050
特别是咆哮的引擎不在你身前
Especially so because the roaring engine was not in front of your nose.

295
00:24:22,051 --> 00:24:23,430
所有噪音都在你身后
All the noise was behind you.

296
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,230
多好的飞机
It is a wonderful thing.

297
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:32,010
飞机的速度极快
The speed was really enormous.

298
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:35,580
飞行特性的优势极大
And the flying characteristics were so advantageous.

299
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:39,720
你坐在飞机里，顿生自信
You actually had a sense of confidence in that machine.

300
00:24:42,210 --> 00:24:46,560
虽然德国飞行员对起飞和速度赞不绝口
Although the German pilots would praise the takeoff and speed at the plane,

301
00:24:46,561 --> 00:24:49,020
但降落比较麻烦
It was the landing that gave them problems.

302
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:55,860
在He109上，飞行员可以关闭引擎缓慢滑行降落
In a 109 plane, one could just switch off the engine and drift done slowly.

303
00:24:55,861 --> 00:24:58,260
但在262上绝无可能
But in this plane it wasn't possible at all.

304
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:04,800
我以400至500英里每小时的速度飞行，而且无法减速
I was traveling at a speed of four hundred and five hundred miles per hour and couldn't reduce it.

305
00:25:04,801 --> 00:25:07,410
这飞机就是不下降
The plane just wouldn't descend.

306
00:25:07,411 --> 00:25:16,350
我看着高度计绕圈飞行，直到3000英尺时才请求降落
I looked at the altitude meter and had to fly in circles until I finally reached an altitude of three thousand feet then asked for permission to land,

307
00:25:16,351 --> 00:25:19,590
我放下起落架，慢慢接近跑道
I lowered the landing gear and slowly approached the runway.

308
00:25:20,730 --> 00:25:24,192
最终我安全降落，如释重负
Finally, I was able to land safely and was greatly relieved.

309
00:25:24,190 --> 00:25:30,060
和往常降落不同，这次我汗流浃背
In contrast to my usual take off in landings, it was completely soaked with sweat.

310
00:25:34,590 --> 00:25:38,460
最初计划是只有王牌飞行员才能驾驶Me-262
Initially, it was planned that only fighter aces would fly the plane,

311
00:25:38,461 --> 00:25:42,390
但4年的战争让帝国空军精锐尽损
But four years of war had taken its toll on Luftwaffe's finest,

312
00:25:42,391 --> 00:25:48,090
那些只有10小时飞行经验的普通飞行员也被征召入伍
So regular pilots, some with as little as ten hours' flying experience were drafted in.

313
00:25:48,091 --> 00:25:53,370
对于新手来说，驾驶Me-262并不简单
But for inexperienced pilots, the EMe-262 was not an easy plan to fly,

314
00:25:53,371 --> 00:25:56,910
超过200名飞行员死于训练
And over two hundred pilots were killed in training alone.

315
00:25:59,161 --> 00:26:03,810
显然，最初的那批人，包括我在内
of course, the first ones to whom I count myself as well.

316
00:26:03,811 --> 00:26:04,590
我们是最好的飞行员
We were the best.

317
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:11,940
但那些后来者基本都是新手，无法操控这种飞机
But those who followed us were often at the beginning of their pilot training and didn't cope with the machine.

318
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:15,810
让他们来驾驶喷气机是完全不负责任的
To put those people in the jet was totally irresponsible.

319
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:19,560
我们损失惨重
We had huge losses there.

320
00:26:22,170 --> 00:26:28,162
1944年中，那些在训练中存活下来的飞行员被送往一个新组建的中队
By mid 1944, those pilots that had survived the training was sent to a newly formed squadrons.

321
00:26:28,162 --> 00:26:33,900
草率地组建成的地勤团队来维护这些精妙的武器
Ground crews too, were hastily recruited to service and maintain these new wonder weapons.

322
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:46,410
通常来说，地勤人员努力工作 确保飞机一直处于就绪状态
Generally speaking, my experience was that the ground crew tried very hard to ensure that the planes were always ready for takeoff.

323
00:26:48,390 --> 00:26:55,980
我对他们不够了解，因为我总是要准备行动或是等待紧急任务
I did not get to know them well enough because I've always had to be ready for action and was waiting for an emergency takeoff.

324
00:26:58,111 --> 00:27:01,380
有时则完全没有任务
Sometimes that was not happen at all.

325
00:27:01,381 --> 00:27:07,110
所以说人的半生都在等待中度过
Hence the saying half of one's life *will waits in vain.

326
00:27:19,350 --> 00:27:21,810
然而等待是短暂的
Yet the waiting was short lived,

327
00:27:21,811 --> 00:27:24,480
随着数千架轰炸机重创德国，
With thousands of bombers now pounding Germany,

328
00:27:24,481 --> 00:27:26,790
每名可用的飞行员都投入行动中
Every available pilots was thrown into action.

329
00:27:50,610 --> 00:27:52,900
1944年7月25日
on July the 25th 1944,

330
00:27:53,100 --> 00:28:01,320
一架Me-262成为首架用于实战的喷气战斗机，
它击落了一架飞过慕尼黑正在拍照的英国蚊式侦察机 
An Me-262 became the first jet airplane to be used in combat when it shot down a British photo reconnaissance mosquito flying over Munich.

331
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:06,280
看来德国赢得了喷气战斗机的竞赛
It now appeared that the race for the jet fighter had been won

332
00:28:06,380 --> 00:28:12,780
*
And with it the prize of victory in the skies, which was now within the Luftwaffe *scruff.

333
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:24,960
1944年夏末，更多的德军飞行员驾驶新Me-262参战
During the late summer of 1944, more and more German Luftwaffe pilots were taking their new Me-262 jet fighters into battle.

334
00:28:24,961 --> 00:28:30,570
似乎德军终于找到了可以击败盟军轰炸机和高速护航战斗机的武器
It seemed as though finally they now had a weapon that could beat the Allied bombers and their high speed escorts.

335
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:38,850
两组四架野马组成紧密队形
There were two groups of four mustangs in close formation,

336
00:28:38,851 --> 00:28:45,300
他们非常自信。但他们没有看见我，这是个失误
And they were so incredibly confident. they hadn't seen me, and that was a mistake.

337
00:28:48,361 --> 00:28:51,060
我为那些没有注意我的人感到遗憾
I actually felt sorry for the guys is they hadn't noticed me.

338
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:54,920
我从右侧低处飞向那里。
I came from deep, low, right and flew in there.

339
00:28:54,960 --> 00:29:00,870
 飞机有4门30mm MK108机炮，火力极强
We had four thirty millimeter guns the MK108,that was an incredible fire,

340
00:29:00,871 --> 00:29:06,330
长长的机翼目标都展现在我面前，不可能打偏
Because the whole thing presented itself to me was a long outstretched point. You couldn't actually miss.

341
00:29:07,410 --> 00:29:09,000
之后就打下了两架战斗机
And then two fighters dropped down.

342
00:29:11,010 --> 00:29:14,700
我看到其中一架飞行员跳伞，另一架则没有
With one I saw a parachute travel with the other one. I didn't.

343
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:17,640
情况就是这样
That was such a case.

344
00:29:21,390 --> 00:29:27,420
1944年末，Me262对盟军轰炸机造成了毁灭性的打击
by late 1944 the 262s were attacking the Allied bombers with devastating effect,

345
00:29:27,421 --> 00:29:31,080
盟军战斗机和轰炸机组不知道如何处理它们
Allied fighter and bomber crews were unsure how to deal with them.

346
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:34,500
它们的速度和火力都过于完美了
Their speed and firepower were just too perfect.

347
00:29:35,610 --> 00:29:40,400
我们一枪也打不中，然后它们就飞走了
We couldn't get a shot. And then he goes.

348
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:43,860
咻~ 再见了您呐~
 Shh~ bye bye fellows~

349
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:49,500
*
And I just said the *grass the crew we just saw a real pilot.

350
00:29:51,000 --> 00:30:03,750
*我们头顶飞过一架Me-262，但只是瞥见了一眼
他从3点钟方向攻击并冲过机群
We were jumped by an Me-262 and only got a very short glimpse of him because he made an attack from about three o'clock high and he came down through the group.

351
00:30:05,060 --> 00:30:07,410
他飞得太快，很难看清楚
He went by so fast, we couldn't hardly see him.

352
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:12,600
这着实令人震惊，因为从未见过这样的飞机
It was really shocked because it was like nothing that we'd seen before.

353
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:19,020
战争早期，德国飞行员还没有体会到自己拥有这样的空中霸权
The German pilots had not felt such supremacy in the air since the early days of the war.

354
00:30:19,021 --> 00:30:25,560
不过他们坚信这种不可思议的飞机可以扭转局势
They felt sure that this incredible plane would turn the tide.

355
00:30:25,561 --> 00:30:31,200
我在德累斯顿区域飞行，下降到16000英尺(4876.8米)
I flew to the area around Dresden and went down to 16,000 feet.

356
00:30:31,201 --> 00:30:35,370
我看见两架战斗机在我上方
I spotted two fighter planes, as they were above me,

357
00:30:35,371 --> 00:30:40,590
我拉升高度，将一架敌机纳入视野
I increased my altitude and I took one of the fighter planes in my sights.

358
00:30:40,591 --> 00:30:43,860
当时，机枪和机炮都是自动开启的
In those days, the machine guns and cannons were automatically switched on.

359
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:49,680
四门机炮喷出一串火舌
I had four cannons and I gave off a burst of fire.

360
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:53,685
*在我意识到命中之前，敌机飞行员就跳伞了
And before I knew it, the pilot parachuted out of his plane.

361
00:30:53,940 --> 00:30:55,740
我甚至都不知道打中了哪里
Where I had hit him I did not know.

362
00:30:57,240 --> 00:30:59,670
一切都是全新的，我就感觉到快
It was all very new, much too fast.

363
00:31:03,721 --> 00:31:06,630
突然我看到了第二架敌机在我前方
And then suddenly I saw the second fighter plane in front of me.

364
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:09,300
我向他开火
And I fired at it,

365
00:31:09,301 --> 00:31:12,990
他被旗帜一样的烟雾包围着坠落
and it went down, surrounded by smoke that looked like a flag.

366
00:31:16,290 --> 00:31:20,190
但轰炸机才是Me-262的首要猎物
But it was the bombers that were the Me-262's real prey.

367
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:27,330
德军飞行员艾尔弗雷德在执行他的第13次任务
一次例行巡逻中碰见了B-17轰炸机
Luftwaffe pilot, Alfred Arms was on a routine patrol when he came across a B-17 on its 13th mission.

368
00:31:29,401 --> 00:31:35,820
没有过多讨论，每个人就选定了目标
Everyone quickly chose a plane without having any great discussions about whether they were going to take this or the other plane.

369
00:31:35,821 --> 00:31:39,510
替代讨论的办法是：说明自己最佳的进攻位置
Instead, you would say the best position for me is the one in the middle.

370
00:31:40,261 --> 00:31:43,470
空中有很多敌机，因此很容易就能选择一个目标
There were enough planes in the sky, which made it easy to pick one.

371
00:31:45,090 --> 00:31:50,130
在那架B-17上的后射手正是19岁的克雷格
The rear gunner in that particular B-17 was nineteen year old Craig Bennett.

372
00:31:50,131 --> 00:31:52,140
他太快了
He came so fast.

373
00:31:52,141 --> 00:31:56,640
你只能扣动扳机，立马开火
all you had time was just pull the triggers and let the guns fire.

374
00:32:05,100 --> 00:32:07,920
我瞄准了突然出现在前方的B-17（绰号：“飞行堡垒”）
I was aiming at a fortress when suddenly ahead of me,

375
00:32:07,921 --> 00:32:14,850
*中队队长被卷入巨大的火墙中，其他人也消失了
There was a large wall of fire into which the captain of my squadron and others disappeared.

376
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:20,220
第一架飞机是领队，他袭击了我们的飞机
The first plane was the leader and he hit our plane.

377
00:32:22,740 --> 00:32:24,390
飞机就这样爆炸了
The plane just blew up.

378
00:32:24,391 --> 00:32:27,210
*
The whole *plane exploded his plane and ours. 

379
00:32:31,531 --> 00:32:34,920
我得以从火墙上飞过
I was able to fly over the wall of fire.

380
00:32:34,921 --> 00:32:41,220
原来，B-17爆炸会让附近范围都处在火焰中
It turned out that the fortress had exploded and taken to adjacent flames with that.

381
00:32:41,221 --> 00:32:43,530
这就是B-17爆炸的威力
That's how big the explosion was.

382
00:32:48,870 --> 00:32:50,370
机尾开始碎裂
And the tail broke off.

383
00:32:51,690 --> 00:32:53,490
飞机开始坠落
and started falling.

384
00:32:54,450 --> 00:32:56,550
其余的机体都消失了
And the rest of the plane was gone.

385
00:32:58,380 --> 00:33:00,620
*
I was the only one they'd *gather my aircraft.

386
00:33:02,010 --> 00:33:05,040
克雷格在接下来的战争期间成为俘虏
Craig Bennett was to spend the rest of the war a POWs.

387
00:33:08,940 --> 00:33:11,640
但这并不是一边倒的战斗
Yet it was not all a one-sided fight.

388
00:33:11,641 --> 00:33:14,280
对这些神奇武器感到震惊的同时,
Once they got over the shock of these new wonder weapons,

389
00:33:14,281 --> 00:33:18,600
盟军飞行员开始逐渐掌握对付德军喷气机的办法
the Allied pilots slowly began to learn how to deal with the German jet.

390
00:33:18,601 --> 00:33:22,381
首要的问题就是如何克服速度上的巨大劣势
The first problem was how to overcome the huge speed disadvantage.

391
00:33:22,381 --> 00:33:26,220
飞行员发现当野马战斗机进入垂直俯冲状态，
The pilot's found that when they put the Mustang into a steep dive,

392
00:33:26,221 --> 00:33:28,770
他们就能和Me-262有相同的速度
their speed was the same as the Me-262.

393
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:32,760
因此我把油门推到底
So I just bent the throttle as far as it could forward,

394
00:33:32,761 --> 00:33:34,350
*一刻不停
*without going through the stop.

395
00:33:35,370 --> 00:33:36,090
接下来
And?

396
00:33:38,430 --> 00:33:44,610
因为他在做一点转向，所以能非常缓慢地接近他
Slowly, very, very slowly start *gaining along the guy because he was making a little turn.

397
00:33:44,611 --> 00:33:46,710
每当他转向一点，我就能逐渐接近
And each time you turn a little bit, I get a little closer.

398
00:33:50,190 --> 00:33:51,760
这家伙是个新手
this guy was inexperienced.

399
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:59,250
我很确信，因为他看见第一架敌机时既没有飞过去也没有出手攻击
*I'm sure because when he saw the first tracers,either *go by him or hit his airplane.

400
00:33:59,251 --> 00:34:00,660
而是开始转向
He made a turn.

401
00:34:00,661 --> 00:34:03,300
如果他把机头朝下，我们怎么才能逃走呢
If you to put his nose down, how do we run?

402
00:34:03,301 --> 00:34:04,080
我们可能就被击落了
We probably never got.

403
00:34:05,550 --> 00:34:07,020
这是一段敌机进入我方射程的影片
A movie where we got in range.

404
00:34:10,410 --> 00:34:16,200
盟军飞行员也发现Me-262的机动能力不如螺旋桨飞机
The Allied pilots also found that the Me-262 did not respond as quick in a turn as propeller planes.

405
00:34:17,100 --> 00:34:18,870
这个影响是致命的
This would have deadly consequences.

406
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:29,040
我位于他转向圈的内侧时，就可以像打靶一样射击它的头部
I was on the inside of his circle and I was able to get a bead on him and shoot in front of him,

407
00:34:29,041 --> 00:34:30,960
这样他就会自己撞上子弹
so he would fly into the bullets.

408
00:34:36,780 --> 00:34:41,070
但Me-262最脆弱的还是起飞和降落的时候
But it was on takeoff and landing at the Me-262, with at its most vulnerable.

409
00:34:42,150 --> 00:34:45,600
盟军飞行员埋伏在机场附近
Allied pilots lay in wait around the airfields.

410
00:34:45,601 --> 00:34:49,380
上百名Me-262飞行员死于这种袭击方式
Hundreds of 262 pilots were to dine In this way.

411
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:57,390
美国人改变策略，专注于驻扎喷气机的机场
The Americans change their tactics to concentrate on all airfields, where jet fighter units were stationed.

412
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:02,760
